summary: Soft Villanelle headcanons: she loves poetry! She enjoys reading villanelles, which were the inspiration for the name she chose...
question: Soft Villanelle headcanons: she loves poetry! She enjoys reading villanelles, which were the inspiration for the name she chose for herself. Every time she's learning a new language she reads poems written in it. She already has a list of poems that she would love to read to Eve
answer:
every time after they have sex, villanelle whispers french into eve’s hair. soft murmers against her scalp. they thrum through her veins, filling her entire body with warmth.

on a particularly quiet night in the countryside, crickets chirping underneath the windowsill, buggy lullabies as they drift to sleep, eve asks villanelle what she’s saying. villanelle smiles. the softest of smiles, reserved only for eve. she recites the words in french again:

Demain, dès l’aube, à l’heure où blanchit la campagne,

Je partirai. Vois-tu, je sais que tu m’attends.

J’irai par la forêt, j’irai par la montagne.

Je ne puis demeurer loin de toi plus longtemps.


Je marcherai les yeux fixés sur mes pensées,

Sans rien voir au dehors, sans entendre aucun bruit,

Seul, inconnu, le dos courbé, les mains croisées,

Triste, et le jour pour moi sera comme la nuit.


Je ne regarderai ni l’or du soir qui tombe,

Ni les voiles au loin descendant vers Harfleur,

Et quand j’arriverai, je mettrai sur ta tombe

Un bouquet de houx vert et de bruyère en fleur.


then in english:


Tomorrow, at dawn, at the hour when the countryside whitens,

I will depart. You see, I know you wait for me.

I will go through the forest and over the mountains.

I cannot stay far from you any longer.


I will trudge on, my eyes fixed on my thoughts,

Ignoring everything around me, without hearing a sound,

Alone, unknown, back stooped, hands crossed,

Saddened, and the day will be like night for me.


I will neither see the golden glow of the falling evening,

Nor the sails going down to Harfleur in the distance,

And when I arrive, I will place on your tomb

A bouquet of green holly and flowering heather.


it was the first poem anna showed in her in french. it’s about the poet visiting his daughter’s grave. she’s always thought it was hauntingly beautiful. villanelle follows in a smaller voice that if she ever returns to russia, she plans on putting a bouquet of holly and heather on anna’s grave.

eve asks villanelle if she knows anymore poems. villanelle says she does. she knows so many. eve wants to hear them all.

summary: tbh, no matter villanelle's backstory, i don't think the show would ever try to make the way she is about trauma. i don't think...
question: tbh, no matter villanelle's backstory, i don't think the show would ever try to make the way she is about trauma. i don't think the purpose of her eventual backstory will be to excuse or even explain her tendencies themselves, i p much expect it to just flesh out where her likes/dislikes are coming from and why her tendencies manifest the way they do, not to question if they'd exist in the first place, or, god forbid, if they can be cured or some bs like that
answer: i agree!! killing eve is one of very few shows where i actually trust the writers (so far…we’re praying for a good s2) so i don’t think they would ever try to excuse her actions. i’m not really, like, Afraid that they’ll try to explain them in s2, it’s just something i really appreciate about the show that they haven’t explained her. what you described is pretty much what i want from the show :)

summary: I love Villanelle and Irina's relationship and hope they bring Irina back at some point. Even for one episode! Am I the only one...
question: I love Villanelle and Irina's relationship and hope they bring Irina back at some point. Even for one episode! Am I the only one who got the feeling Villanelle wouldn't have actually hurt her?
answer:
i would imagine the one point at which irina was actually at risk was when villanelle was face to face with konstantin, because i think villanelle would feel that if it comes down to her or irina then her own life matters more. although even then villanelle chose to take a shot at konstantin and then let irina get away, so. who knows!

the rest of the time though i would agree that villanelle’s interactions with irina are pretty transparently based on empty threats when you compare them to the way she threatens other people. villanelle when she is actually intending to hurt someone tends to be very… confident and predatory whereas with irina it was much more just her kind of, getting frustrated and defensive and bristle-y and showboat-y. she doesn’t even try to rough irina up to get her to cooperate, she just kind of… drags irina around and keeps her fed and teaches her how to con people and huffs when irina annoys her. i don’t know if that’s more due to whatever moral code she does have or because she cared enough about konstantin to want to avoid hurting his daughter, but it’s interesting either way!

i would agree that i’d love to see more of them together, though…
